Really?!?<p>How can you guarantee that the component library that your company just bought, available only in binary form isn&#x27;t doing something like this?<p><pre><code>    void cool_stuff_with_widget(const std::shared_ptr<UI> ptr)
    {
       UI* evilPtr = const_cast<UI*>(ptr->get());
       // now store evilPtr somewhere else and try to use it any time the library feels like it
    }

</code></pre>
No one is going through disassembly to check such behaviors.<p>C++ RC is a very welcoming addition to the language, but it only works if everyone plays by the rules, 100% of the time.
